snippet: Parking spaces are at a premium in cities like Boston, but they reached a new level at an auction Thursday, when the bidding for two adjoining spaces ended at $560,000.
abstract: Auction for adjacent parking spaces in Boston ends with spaces being sold for $560,000, shattering previous record for prices of parking space; parking space is at a premium in cities like Boston, and prices have been climbing for years.
lead_paragraph: Parking spaces are at a premium in cities like Boston, but they reached a new level at an auction Thursday, when the bidding for two adjoining spaces ended at $560,000.

headline.seo: Two Boston Parking Spots Sell for $560,000 at Auction
